## 2. Breakdown Point Score (BPS) Matrix

### 2.1 Risk Category Definitions

| Risk ID | Category | Description | Weight (λ) |
|---------|----------|-------------|------------|
| R001 | DATA_INTEGRITY | Input data corruption/staleness | 0.25 |
| R002 | MODEL_DRIFT | Classification accuracy degradation | 0.20 |
| R003 | LATENCY_BREACH | Response time SLA violation | 0.15 |
| R004 | THROUGHPUT_COLLAPSE | Request processing capacity failure | 0.15 |
| R005 | DEPENDENCY_FAILURE | Upstream/downstream service outage | 0.10 |
| R006 | RESOURCE_EXHAUSTION | Memory/CPU/storage depletion | 0.10 |
| R007 | SECURITY_BREACH | Authentication/authorization failure | 0.05 |

### 2.2 BPS Calculation Matrix

```
BPS(t) = Σᵢ₌₁⁷ λᵢ · Pᵢ(t) · Iᵢ

Where:
- λᵢ = risk weight from table above
- Pᵢ(t) = probability of risk i at time t
- Iᵢ = impact severity [1-10]

Operational State Thresholds:
- BPS < 2.0  → NOMINAL
- BPS ∈ [2.0, 4.0) → DEGRADED
- BPS ∈ [4.0, 7.0) → CRITICAL
- BPS ≥ 7.0 → FAILURE
```

### 2.3 Full BPS Matrix

