└─────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┴────────┘
```

### 2.4 Cascading Failure Probability

```
P_cascade(n) = 1 - ∏ᵢ₌₁ⁿ (1 - Pᵢ · Cᵢⱼ)

Where:
- Cᵢⱼ = correlation coefficient between risk i and j
- n = number of active risk factors

Correlation Matrix Cᵢⱼ:
     R001  R002  R003  R004  R005  R006  R007
R001 1.00  0.65  0.20  0.15  0.30  0.25  0.10
R002 0.65  1.00  0.35  0.25  0.20  0.15  0.05
R003 0.20  0.35  1.00  0.80  0.45  0.70  0.15
R004 0.15  0.25  0.80  1.00  0.50  0.75  0.10
R005 0.30  0.20  0.45  0.50  1.00  0.40  0.20
R006 0.25  0.15  0.70  0.75  0.40  1.00  0.15
R007 0.10  0.05  0.15  0.10  0.20  0.15  1.00
```

